article.headline: Loyola (MD) 94, Siena 87 (OT)
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Gerald Brown scored 33 points to lead Loyola in a 94-87 win over Siena Tuesday. Kenny Hasbrouck scored 29, and Michael Haddix contributed 23 points and 12 rebounds for the Saints (8-6, 4-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Loyola (8-6, 4-1) shot 63 percent from the floor in overtime and outscored Siena 20-13 after regulation. The Greyhounds made 11-of-22 3-pointers and out-rebounded Siena 42-34. Michael Tuck came off the bench to score 12 of is 15 points in the second half, including a 3-pointer that gave Loyola a 72-71 lead with three minutes remaining. Edwin Ubiles responded with a quick three, but Brown answered with a lay-up to tie the score at 74-74. The teams pushed the game into overtime, as neither side scored in the final 1:26 of regulation play. With the score tied 78-78 one minute into the extra session, Loyola scored the next six points and never trailed again. Brett Harvey hit a 3-pointer and Tuck converted a 3-point play to help the Greyhounds seize control. Siena had won nine straight MAAC games dating back to last season and entered the game as the MAAC's only undefeated team.
